However, the most important thing about this patch, imo, has been royally F'd up.<br>
<br>
Was the point of removing the flags to let people who haven't put in the time to get flagged, XP in them as normal? NO. The point here, was that people who had not made it to Guild_raid_0023, would still be able to accompany the guild on the next raid - a raid that previously would have <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>required</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> that they attend the previous raid, and get flagged for the current encounter. Removing the flags to enter these zones, but not removing the flagging requirement for advancing to encounters at the SolRo Tower level and beyond, is completely devoid of all reason and logic. Have they fixed, AT ALL, the problem guilds were having with backflagging? NO. If guildmember_004 misses guild_raid_37, he STILL MUST be a thorn in the guild's side and have them do the entire encounter over - till they do, guildmember_004 will not be able to go on any events past this, since he will not be receiving the flag for them, or may not even have the flag yet to come along.<br>
<br>
